<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Schizanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. porrigens" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="porrigens" subSpecies="porrigens">subsp. porrigens</taxonomicName>
in its uniform corolla colour, with or without one faint dark spot in the upper part of each lateral lobe (in the separation of the lateral and middle lobe). These spots do not reach the margin of the lobes. A white halo always surrounding the yellow area of the upper middle lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
